print ("In Python, dates and times are handled using the datetime module, which allows programs to work with real-world concepts like days, months, years, and time.")
print (" A date can represent a specific calendar day, while a time can include hours, minutes, and seconds." )
print (" Using dates is important for tasks such as tracking deadlines, calculating ages, logging events, or measuring how much time has passed.")
print (" Python makes it easy to get the current date and time, compare two dates, or find the difference between them, which is often returned as a time span (for example, the number of days between two dates).")
print (" Python also includes powerful tools for mathematics, both built-in and through the math module.")
print (" Basic math operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, exponents, and modulus are built directly into the language and work with numbers such as integers and floats.")
print (" For more advanced mathematical operations, the math module provides functions like square roots, powers, rounding, absolute values, and trigonometric functions.")
print (" These tools are especially useful in scientific calculations, geometry, physics, data analysis, and problem-solving tasks.")
print (" Together, Python’s date-handling features and math capabilities allow programs to model real-life situations accurately.")
print (" Dates help manage time-based data and events, while math enables precise calculations and logical problem solving.")
print (" Mastering both is essential for writing practical programs that can analyze data, make predictions, and automate tasks that depend on time and numerical reasoning.")
